# Wallet secrets for the cross-VM testing framework.
#
# ONLY secrets live here. The wallet roster (labels, account indices, and how each wallet
# sources its key) is the compile-time roster const built with `define_wallet_roster!`, not this
# file. Each row picks one of three `WalletSource` variants:
#
#   env_mnemonic("VAR")     reads a BIP-39 phrase from variable VAR (derives via index / HD path)
#   auto                    generates a fresh random mnemonic at build time (no env var; mock chains)
#   env_private_key("VAR")  reads a raw private key from variable VAR (hex on EVM/Cosmos, base58 on Solana)
#
# `from_roster` keeps each row's source and resolves it on use, reading these variables from the
# process environment then, so load this file first (e.g. `dotenvy::from_path(".env")`). An
# `env_mnemonic` / `env_private_key` variable is read lazily: an unset var only errors when a test
# signs with that wallet, not at construction. Copy this file to `.env` and replace the values.
#
# The values below are the canonical BIP-39 test vector (publicly known, never use on mainnet).

# Backs the `test` wallet (index 0 = m/44'/60'/0'/0/0) used by the live on-chain tests
# (crates/solidity/tests/onchain.rs, crates/cosmwasm/tests/onchain.rs) and the deploy_counter
# script. Use a REAL mnemonic whose index-0 address you have funded on the target testnet.
MNEMONIC_TEST="<your funded testnet mnemonic>"

# Backs the `on_chain` wallet (index 0) used by the live `rpc-endurance` counter endurance run
# against Base Sepolia (examples/integration-tests, `make test-rpc-endurance`). Resolved lazily, so
# only needed for that run. Use a REAL mnemonic whose index-0 address you have funded on Base Sepolia.
ON_CHAIN_WALLET="<your funded Base Sepolia mnemonic>"

# Example raw private key source, for a hypothetical `env_private_key("PRIVKEY_SIGNER")` row.
# EVM/Cosmos expect hex (with or without a 0x prefix); Solana expects a base58 keypair string.
# PRIVKEY_SIGNER="0x59c6995e998f97a5a0044966f0945389dc9e86dae88c7a8412f4603b6b78690d"
